to answer her question properly anyway.

381
00:31:53,995 --> 00:31:55,955
To be honest, we all know that

382
00:31:56,039 --> 00:31:58,833
there aren't many things in life

383
00:31:58,917 --> 00:32:00,293
that truly make us happy.

384
00:32:00,376 --> 00:32:03,171
We also tend to look on the bright side

385
00:32:04,464 --> 00:32:07,300
to guard that rarely found happiness,

386
00:32:07,383 --> 00:32:08,718
so as to keep it in mind.

387
00:32:11,429 --> 00:32:14,307
<i>Recently, I encountered something</i>
<i>that made me realize</i>

388
00:32:15,308 --> 00:32:17,310
<i>that a lot of the time, we feel unhappy,</i>

389
00:32:18,311 --> 00:32:20,980
<i>maybe because we're too eager to hold onto</i>

390
00:32:21,064 --> 00:32:24,359
<i>those happy moments</i>
<i>we're so obsessed with.</i>

391
00:32:25,735 --> 00:32:28,488
<i>If we want to feel that happiness again,</i>

392
00:32:29,280 --> 00:32:30,990
<i>the only thing we can do</i>

393
00:32:31,783 --> 00:32:33,660
<i>is perhaps let go.</i>

394
00:32:35,036 --> 00:32:37,372
<i>Let the happiness we couldn't keep</i>

395
00:32:37,914 --> 00:32:39,332
<i>remain in the past.</i>

396
00:32:40,959 --> 00:32:43,002
<i>All right, just a few more hours,</i>

397
00:32:43,086 --> 00:32:45,088
<i>and this Monday will be over.</i>

398
00:32:45,171 --> 00:32:46,714
<i>We can do this.</i>

399
00:32:47,215 --> 00:32:50,843
<i>Let's forget the happy moments in the past</i>
<i>that we're obsessed with</i>

400
00:32:51,344 --> 00:32:54,263
<i>and listen to some music that suits today.</i>

